description:
The Wine Show - Series 1, Episode 9




From their villa HQ in the Italian hills, Matthew Goode and Matthew Rhys head to Verona, the setting for Romeo and Juliet, where they practice their new sommelier skills on two unsuspecting lovers. Amelia Singer attempts to persuade Joe Fattorini that there is more to port than a drink at Christmas, before they cruise up the Douro to visit one of England's oldest wine families who are at the forefront of Portugal's wine revolution. Chef Niki Nakayama chooses a Japanese sake as her favourite wine, and creates a dish to match it.




Original Air Date: 26-Jun-2016
